para_trans: Government Decision No: Committee-2,424 / P.No.80 / Health-5
The activities and objectives of the District Level Committee are:
1. Analyzing the epidemiological situation in the district and determining the cause of the outbreak.
Preventive and control measures to be taken should be outlined.
2. Study the existing epidemic control system in the district and make necessary changes in it.
to suggest.
3. By making a comparative study of the epidemiological situation in the neighbouring district of the district.
Accordingly, issues of inter-district coordination should be decided.
4. Implementation of guidelines at state and central level.
5. Each department in an epidemic in consultation with the other department for epidemic prevention.
Determine the role and act accordingly.
6. As per the guidelines of the Central Government. Consolidated by Government Decision of 25.03.2019
